LAGOS – Super Eagles and Leganes defender, Kenneth Omeruo’s football academy have com­pleted transfer of two young players, Obi Martins and Samuel Obaleh to the Spanish Segunda club, Leganes. The player confirmed this on Thursday at the Catho­lic Church playing Ground, Gwarimpa, Abuja, where scouting for talented young players is currently ongoing. Looking back to over a de­cade, Omeruo thanked God and Coach Abimbola Samu­el, who discovered him at the same pitch, 11 years ago add­ing that he is happy to see his dream of many years coming to reality. He stated that giving young boys the platform to realise their dream of playing profes­sional football gladdened his heart and promised to use his academy help discover talents for Nigeria. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “It is a thing of joy seeing my dream coming to reality. I am happy when my acad­emy facilitated signing of two players (Obi Martins and Samuel Obaleh) to my club, Leganes. “I will like to add that see­ing players from my academy playing for the national team will make me a fulfilled man after my retirement from football. Giving young talent­ed players such platform will help reduce crimes rate, help players take good care of their family and more importantly, takes boys off the streets and give them hope,” he said. 68 Domestic Sponsors Agree To Extend Contracts For Postponed Tokyo Games Ilaji Hotels Set To Host WBF Title Fight Omeruo is optimistic that Leganes will return back to the Spanish LaLiga next sea­son after suffering a relega­tion setback last season. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION